d always wondered how it was that my grandfather and grandmother, who had 13 children \endash  and my mother was the last of 13 \endash  how it was that somebody who ran a draper\rquote 
s shop could be so relatively well-off as to buy a large house, a country house and a town house. He had a small town house, 
but a rather large country house, plus land, near Turriff in Aberdeenshire. And we always wondered how he had managed to do that. I think he must have been speculating or something else \endash 
 not on the Stock Exchange, but on the Agricultural Exchange or something like that. Anyhow, I remember my grandmother, because we used to go up there in the summer holidays, and all the cousins \endash  of which there are many \endash  u}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid855262 sed to gather around the house.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 In Lo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid855262 ndon, I don\rquote t remember anybody.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 My grandfather had departed, h
