whether it was a \lquote Wee Free\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 , I don\rquote t know, but certainly a very Presbyterian household. That was all I remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Paul:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab 
And did your mother continue that sort of Scottishness?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Jack:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab 
Oh, very much. She joined the Post Office in London, as a girl of 16, from Turriff High School. Neither
 of my parents did secondary education, but they were very interested in education. My mother stayed with the Post Office in London until she married. She was a clerk then. In that time, of course, women in the Civil Service couldn\rquote 
t remain when they married, they had to move out. So as a result of this, we \endash  my brother and I \endash  received our mother\rquote 
s attention, which was certainly very Scottish. She emphasised her Scottishness all the time. My son, who is in India, and has long been in India as a Buddhist Missionary, came back and that\rquote 
s when I went out to visit, last year, with my brother and him, and he reminded me that when he went there, he seemed to know more about the old house than I did, because my mother had spoken so much with him about it. She kept
 on. She would never go back there permanently, she said, because it was too cold. What she remembered was the cold winters. But as far as Scottishness and education was concerned, she was very concerned with that, yes. And, of course, having been sacked 
b
y the Post Office when she married, she spent all her time with my brother and I on our education. My brother was a Fellow here too, before he went to Harvard. He told me, the other day, that he thinks we are the only two Fellows of the National Academy o
f Sciences in America, only two brothers, who are Fellows of the National Academy of Sciences in America. So that was as a result of my Scottish upbringing \endash  my semi-Scottish upbringing, and my uneducated mother, and father.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Paul:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab 
