Not that I remember, no. Well, it was important, I suppose, in sort of equipping me ... it was certainly a very good school \endash  the only one in Welwyn at the time, maybe now \endash 
 but there was no secondary school in Welwyn Garden City at that time, and I think the secondary school, in County terms, was probably at Stevenag
e. But my parents decided to send me to St Albans, which was a private school, as a day boy. So I travelled over as a day boy there, and I suppose that was really formative for me, from an intellectual point of view. It was there that I became interested 
in doing something in English, in literature. It was there my brother decided to do something in physics.
\par 
