iend, Frank Fisher, and we were out in the hills, way up in the hills, towards Monte Cassino, not far from it. As I was clearing out my room the other day, I came across an account which Frank \endash  who is now dead \endash 
 had written about him getting through, beca
use we got captured up in the hills, recaptured, by a patrol, and as we were going down the mountainside, Frank managed to run away and escape, and jump down, and I started to follow him, but I heard this German shouting behind me, so I stopped, and I cou
ldn\rquote t get away. But he got down, and he eventually got back through to Monte Cassino, after a number of days \endash  a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14039528 nd got decorated for his pains.  }{
