. So I went and tried the Vatican, well, got somebody else to look it over, and was told there were Germans inside the Vatican, which was true, of course, because of the German Embassy inside, but it was also defended rather well because they didn\rquote 
t want everyone coming in there. So I decided that wasn\rquote t for me. I started walking up through Italy, I was walking up to Switzerland, in the opposite direction from Cassino, but I didn\rquote 
t get very far because my foot troubled me. When I stopped outside Rome, I was directed to go to a nearby house, a small chateau, in fact, where I was told there was a \lquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 principessa Americana}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \rquote 
 who would look after me. So I went there. I didn\rquote t get into the house, because I stayed outside, and a big man came out \endash  a bailiff \endash  with a large dog, asked me what I wanted. Anyhow, eventually I was allowed in to see this }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 principessa Americana}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 
, who turned out to be an American called Jean Perkins, from Boston, and her husband was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 Colonna}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 , a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 Principe Colonna}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
