\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Paul:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 What about other students, then, apart from Godfrey, were there other students who were important in the long run, at Cambridge?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Jack:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab 
Yes, there must have been, but, I\rquote 
m having difficulty with sorting out their years. That particular one was somebody who became the first Professor of Sociology here, a man called John Barnes, who I think was teaching in London at the time, not here. Here, there was Godfrey. There was a m
a
n who eventually later got a lectureship at Manchester, a Welshman called Emrys Peters, who wrote on the Bedouin. Emrys Peters, Godfrey, and Peter Worsley was there somewhere around, he read English, like me, but I think he went to Oxford before. And a wo
man called Kathleen Gough, who also read English, who worked on one of the Nayar in India.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6231102  Shatwick (?? \endash  2.05) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 was there too, at that time. But it\rquote s Godfrey and Emrys that I remember most from that year, and Godfrey ... yes, he influenced me a lot, I think, because he ... he\rquote 
d also read English, whereas Emrys was a geographer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Paul:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab 
