\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Jack:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab 
My first wife? Joan Wright. And I married her in Cambridge [in 1946] when I was finishing my degree, and I first went into education partly because she was very interested in education. She\rquote 
d been at Bedales, she did a thesis on A.S. Neill, so she was very interested in progressive education. We had three children together. That was when I decided that education was not really for me, and I
 took up this Scholarship to go out to Ghana. But it was at that time that my marriage got into problems, and so I remarried some years later to Esther Goody, who went out to Ghana with me, and worked out there, and she\rquote 
s out there now, as far as I know. She was American.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Paul:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab 
