 for publications and that kind of thing \endash  I certainly learnt something about L\'e9vi-Strauss\rquote s structuralism from him, but I was never very taken by that, and he wasn\rquote 
t much taken by my interest in history, or not much by my interest in literacy either. But then neither was Meyer Fortes. And, I mean, not many people have been. I\rquote ve never really had a student who\rquote s been interested in literacy. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Paul:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab That\rquote 
