\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Jack:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab 
Well, it is, but let me say, in France \endash  I\rquote ve just come back from Lyon \endash  wher
e I was invited. I mean, at the beginning of the year, in January, there was a whole three day conference in Lyon, on the work of Jack Goody, or what came out of the work of Jack Goody, with people from all over. But that\rquote 
s never happened to me in this country. And anthropologists, I found, became very committed to their own particular patch \endash  wherever that was \endash 
 and were not really interested in trying to link up these various patches in any historical way or geographical way, for that matter.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1191190\charrsid1191190 Paul:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667 \tab But y
ou, you have an attachment to your patch as well as your comparative approach, don\rquote t you?
