t integrate, whereas I thought that the work I did in my thesis on death and the ancestors, which I read parts of Freud for, as well as parts of Marxist writers on law \endash  thanks to Eric Hobsbawm \endash 
 then I thought that I had used the work on ambivalence, and particularly work about death, in order to do this, in order to integrate in some way. I don\rquote t think many psychologists would recognise this, and particularly Freudian ones, but }{
