hing. But until we got tape recorders like that, you couldn\rquote t see this in purely oral cultures without writing, you couldn\rquote 
t see what the problem was. You wrote down one version of myth, and that was it, and you never went back, because [it was a] long dis
tance away. But [later], what with the aeroplane going backwards and forwards, and with the tape recorder, you could make repeated observations in a certain place, over time, and that seemed, to me, to make an enormous amount of difference. It wasn
\rquote t taken up by too many people, because a lot of people didn\rquote t go back.
