t a woman that was inheriting the property. Daughters inherited from their mothers. Men, in patrilineal societies, passed to their sons, and in matrilineal societies, they went to their sisters\rquote  sons, whereas in Eur
ope you had a different system, even under Salic Law. Women didn\rquote t necessarily inherit, but they were endowed at marriage, they were given their portion \endash  a word which I always thoug}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid1529417 ht was highly significant, \lquote portion\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid677667\charrsid677667  \endash 
