t meant that this large empire was held together by one system of writing. I have seen people from Canton trying to communicate with people from Beijing, and writing down their communication and passing it. They wouldn\rquote 
t understand orally, but they underst
and in writing, so the whole of the bureaucracy, and the whole of the maintaining that huge country together, was really much easier to having a logographic script. And I always like to say that they did that, so they kept their local cultures. Whereas in
 America, it had a large empire, a large country like that, but only through institutionalising English \endash  everything else was brushed away, German, French \endash  everybody had to learn English. You had one language, which you didn\rquote 
