pology at Edinburgh, called Francesca Bray, who was actually a pupil of Joseph Needham, and wrote the book in that Needham Series, on Chinese agriculture. She later became a student of mine, in Anthropology. That was interesting, because she was originall
y
 in Chinese Studies. And there was somebody who was originally in Arabic Studies, a very good Arabist, called Martha Mundy, who is now at LSE, a Professor there. She worked in the Middle East, and knows Arabic and Arabs better than anyone in this country,
 I should think. She spent many years there, in Palestine and Lebanon, Yemen, Syria. She hasn\rquote t written very widely \endash  well, she\rquote s written about the Middle East, but in a rather local way. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
