s got me out of the purely anthropological or sociological ambience, into something wider. So that\rquote s always been an important hobby for me, and I think that\rquote 
s what was important for me in the African Studies Centre, when I could join up with Edward Shils, because I could do as I wanted to then, which is not a given to you in academic life.
